Part 1: Introduction to Python and Setting Up
Objective: Install Python, set up the development environment, and write the first Python script.

1. Install Python:
    - Download and install Python from python.org.

2. Set Up a Development Environment:
    - Install an Integrated Development Environment (IDE) like VSCode, PyCharm, or use an online editor like Replit.

First Python Script:
Write a simple script that prints "Hello, World!".

Exercise:
Modify the script to print your name and your favorite hobby.